sh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William de Chabbonare I was born in 1174, in Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 son. He died in Bodenham, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1174–":"1174–Surnud","1192–Male":"1192–Surnud","1174–Male":"1174–Surnud","1175":"1175","1174":"1174","1192":"1192","Woebley Castle, Bodenham, Herefordshire, England":"Bodenham, Herefordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Chabbenor Manor, Herefordshire, England":"Herefordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1174–":"1174–Kuollut","1192–Male":"1192–Kuollut","1174–Male":"1174–Kuollut","1175":"1175","1174":"1174","1192":"1192","Woebley Castle, Bodenham, Herefordshire, England":"Bodenham, Herefordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Chabbenor Manor, Herefordshire, England":"Herefordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1174–":"1174–Décédé","1192–Male":"1192–Décédé","1174–Male":"1174–Décédé","1175":"1175","1174":"1174","1192":"1192","Woebley Castle, Bodenham, Herefordshire, England":"Bode